
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gcov-tool-12` baraye analiz kardan data-ye code coverage ke az instrument shodan code ba gcov gerefte shode estefade mishavad. In tool be shoma komak mikonad ke bebinid kodam khat-ha az code-e shoma execute shode va kodam khat-ha execute nashode ast, va behtar test case benevisid. `12` neshan dahande version-e GCC (GNU Compiler Collection) ast.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help`       --> ℹ️ Namayesh rahnamaye tool va gozine-haye mojud.
    🔹 `--version`    --> 📦 Namayesh version-e `gcov-tool-12`.
    🔹 `--gcov-prefix DIR` --> 📂 Directory-e asli baraye file-haye `.gcno` va `.gcda`.
    🔹 `--object-directory DIR` --> 📁 Directory-e asli baraye object file-ha.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gcov-tool-12 --help

    🔹 Namayesh rahnamaye dastoor.

    $ gcov-tool-12 --version

    🔹 Namayesh version-e `gcov-tool-12`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gcov-tool-12 --gcov-prefix build/ --object-directory obj/

    🔹 Be `gcov-tool-12` migooyad ke file-haye `.gcno` va `.gcda` ra az `build/` va object file-ha ra az `obj/` begirad baraye mohasebeye coverage.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gcov-tool-12` command is used to analyze code coverage data generated by instrumenting code with gcov.  This tool helps you see which lines of your code were executed and which lines were not, allowing you to write better test cases. The `12` indicates the GCC (GNU Compiler Collection) version.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help`       --> ℹ️ Display the tool's help information and available options.
    🔹 `--version`    --> 📦 Display the version of `gcov-tool-12`.
    🔹 `--gcov-prefix DIR` --> 📂 Set the base directory for `.gcno` and `.gcda` files.
    🔹 `--object-directory DIR` --> 📁 Set the base directory for object files.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gcov-tool-12 --help

    🔹 Display the command's help information.

    $ gcov-tool-12 --version

    🔹 Display the version of `gcov-tool-12`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gcov-tool-12 --gcov-prefix build/ --object-directory obj/

    🔹 Tells `gcov-tool-12` to find the `.gcno` and `.gcda` files in `build/` and object files in `obj/` for calculating code coverage.
